{"type":"run_title","message":"Task: Web UI logs don't match CLI logs — shows wrong content","timestamp":"2026-03-11T00:07:00.053478971Z"}
{"type":"step_started","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-11T00:07:00.053664572Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"All tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:","timestamp":"2026-03-11T00:11:57.940034589Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-11T00:11:57.940078392Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"**Root cause:** When the web UI requested step-specific output (e.g., `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/implement/output`), and the per-step log file (`implement.log`) was missing, the handler fell back to serving the **entire** `container.log` — which contains unfiltered, mixed output from ALL steps. This caused the web UI to show content from other steps (like a \"limit reached\" error) when viewing a specific step's logs. The CLI didn't hit this path because `cloche logs` defaults to reading `full.log` as a unified stream.","timestamp":"2026-03-11T00:11:57.940081468Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-11T00:11:57.940094753Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"**Changes:**","timestamp":"2026-03-11T00:11:57.940097508Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"1. **`internal/adapters/web/handler.go`** — Removed the `container.log` and live docker logs fallbacks from `handleAPIStepOutput`. Now returns 404 when a step-specific log file doesn't exist, rather than serving wrong content.","timestamp":"2026-03-11T00:11:57.940099852Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"2. **`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** — Removed the same `container.log` fallback from the gRPC `StreamLogs` capture-based path for consistency.","timestamp":"2026-03-11T00:11:57.94010385Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"3. **Tests updated:** Renamed `TestServer_StreamLogs_FallsBackToContainerLog` to `TestServer_StreamLogs_DoesNotFallBackToContainerLog` and verified the new behavior. Added three new web handler tests (`TestStepOutput_ReturnsStepLog`, `TestStepOutput_DoesNotFallBackToContainerLog`, `TestStepOutput_DoesNotFallBackToLiveDockerLogs`).","timestamp":"2026-03-11T00:11:57.940107407Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-11T00:11:57.940110994Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"CLOCHE_RESULT:success","timestamp":"2026-03-11T00:11:58.252381509Z"}
